
Week 1 – Python Fundamentals

Spent the week getting introduced to Python by following the provided resources. Started with the SSL slides for a high-level overview, then worked through the W3Schools Python tutorial to build a solid foundation. Covered core Python concepts including variables, data types, control flow (if/else, loops), functions, and basic data structures (lists, tuples, dictionaries). The focus was on conceptual understanding rather than memorizing syntax. No formal assignments were given for this week.

